                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15515361" author="ram_krish" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2016 04:22:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this a bug or is it a valid case? So in case of puts that gets buffered and the client dies even then those puts are not considered to be successful (as autoflush is false). In that case also any get() won&apos;t return those results correct?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15515743" author="anoop.hbase" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2016 08:01:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ya some thing can be considered as committed only after the flush (when deferred flush)  And as per HBase consistency model, any reader can view only fully committed data. Dont think this is a bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15521779" author="allan163" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2016 01:50:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This problem should have been fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15811&quot; title=&quot;Batch Get after batch Put does not fetch all Cells&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15811&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-15811&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15521881" author="stack" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2016 03:01:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah.  What &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=allan163&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;allan163&quot;&gt;Allan Yang&lt;/a&gt; said. This is a duplicate of hbase-15811?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15522066" author="ram_krish" created="Mon, 26 Sep 2016 05:05:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see. So even if autoflush is disabled then &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15811&quot; title=&quot;Batch Get after batch Put does not fetch all Cells&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15811&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-15811&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixes it. Let me check it. Thanks for the info.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
